---
import TimeSkipLayout from '../../layouts/TimeSkipLayout.astro';
---

<TimeSkipLayout 
  title="Privacy Policy — TimeSkip" 
  description="TimeSkip Privacy Policy. Learn how we protect your data while you time-travel through social media."
  canonicalPath="/timeskip/privacy"
>
  <div class="ts-wrap">
    <div class="ts-legal">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="ts-subtitle">Last updated: June 25, 2026</p>

      <p>
        TimeSkip ("<strong>we</strong>," "<strong>us</strong>," or "<strong>our</strong>") operates the TimeSkip browser extension for Google Chrome and Microsoft Edge, as well as the website
        <a href="https://thinkmodeplus.com/timeskip">thinkmodeplus.com/timeskip</a> (collectively, the "<strong>Service</strong>"). This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and the choices you have.
      </p>
      <p>
        By installing the extension or using our website you agree to the practices described in this policy. If you do not agree, please uninstall the extension and discontinue use of the website.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

      <h3>1.1 Information You Provide</h3>
      <p>
        When you create an account, you may provide us with an email address and password. Payment information is processed entirely by <strong>Dodo Payments</strong> — we never see or store your full credit card number.
      </p>

      <h3>1.2 Extension Settings (Chrome Storage)</h3>
      <p>
        TimeSkip stores your extension preferences (such as usage counters and subscription status) using the Chrome Storage API. This data is tied to your browser profile. We do not transmit this data to our own servers.
      </p>

      <h3>1.3 Profile Information Accessed</h3>
      <p>
        When you visit an X (Twitter) profile page, TimeSkip reads two pieces of publicly visible information from the page DOM: the <strong>username</strong> and <strong>join date</strong>. This information is used solely to construct search URLs and is never transmitted to any server.
      </p>

      <h3>1.4 What We Do <em>Not</em> Collect</h3>
      <p>We are committed to minimal data collection. TimeSkip does <strong>not</strong> collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your browsing history or the URLs you visit (beyond the current profile page)</li>
        <li>The content of tweets, DMs, or any private messages</li>
        <li>Your X/Twitter account credentials or session tokens</li>
        <li>Personal data such as your name, phone number, or physical address</li>
        <li>Keystroke or mouse-tracking data</li>
        <li>Analytics or telemetry data from the extension</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
      <p>The limited information we do process is used exclusively to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Provide the Service</strong> — construct search URLs, track daily usage limits, and authenticate your subscription status.</li>
        <li><strong>Process payments</strong> — manage subscriptions and billing through Dodo Payments.</li>
        <li><strong>Communicate with you</strong> — send transactional emails related to your account. We do not send marketing emails unless you explicitly opt in.</li>
        <li><strong>Improve the Service</strong> — diagnose technical issues and improve reliability. Any debugging data is aggregated and anonymized.</li>
        <li><strong>Comply with legal obligations</strong> — respond to lawful requests from authorities when required by applicable law.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>

      <h3>3.1 Chrome Web Store</h3>
      <p>TimeSkip is distributed through the Chrome Web Store, which is operated by Google. Google's <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> governs the collection and use of data by the Chrome Web Store.</p>

      <h3>3.2 Dodo Payments</h3>
      <p>We use Dodo Payments to process subscription payments. When you purchase a paid plan, your payment information is collected and processed directly by Dodo Payments. We receive only your email address and subscription status — never your card details.</p>

      <h3>3.3 X (Twitter) Advanced Search</h3>
      <p>TimeSkip constructs search URLs using X's publicly available Advanced Search feature. All queries are executed in your browser as if you typed them into the X search bar yourself. We do not use any Twitter API, scraping tools, or hidden endpoints.</p>

      <h3>3.4 Supabase</h3>
      <p>We use Supabase for user authentication and subscription management. Supabase stores your email address and hashed password. Your data is hosted on secure, SOC 2-compliant servers.</p>

      <h2>4. Cookies & Local Storage</h2>
      <p>The TimeSkip website uses minimal cookies related to Supabase authentication sessions. The extension stores data locally in Chrome's storage API. We do not use third-party tracking cookies, advertising cookies, or analytics scripts.</p>

      <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
      <p>We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your information, including encrypted data transmission (HTTPS/TLS) and secure authentication via Supabase. However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

      <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>We retain your account information (email and subscription status) for as long as your account is active. If you delete your account, we will remove your personal information within 30 days, except where we are required by law to retain it.</p>

      <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>TimeSkip is not intended for users under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we become aware that we have inadvertently collected data from a child under 13, we will delete it promptly.</p>

      <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>

      <h3>8.1 GDPR (European Users)</h3>
      <p>If you are located in the European Economic Area, you have the right to access, rectify, erase, restrict processing, port, and object to the processing of your personal data. To exercise these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:vypur24@gmail.com">vypur24@gmail.com</a>.</p>

      <h3>8.2 CCPA (California Users)</h3>
      <p>If you are a California resident, you have the right to know what personal information we collect, request deletion of your data, and opt out of the sale of your personal information. We do not sell personal information. To exercise these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:vypur24@gmail.com">vypur24@gmail.com</a>.</p>

      <h2>9. International Data Transfers</h2>
      <p>Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your country of residence. We ensure appropriate safeguards are in place to protect your data in compliance with applicable data protection laws.</p>

      <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make material changes, we will notify you by posting the updated policy on this page with a new "Last updated" date. Your continued use of the Service after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.</p>

      <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:vypur24@gmail.com">vypur24@gmail.com</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</TimeSkipLayout>
